        <div className="bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 p-6 rounded-3xl flex gap-4">
            <div className="bg-indigo-100 p-3 rounded-2xl flex-shrink-0 h-fit">
                <Info className="text-indigo-600" size={24} />
            </div>
            <div>
                <h4 className="font-bold text-indigo-900 mb-2">Requirement: Min Soil Plan Dimension</h4>
                <p className="text-sm text-indigo-800 leading-relaxed">
                    Soil volume is not the only metric. To ensure structural stability for large canopy trees, Table B defines a **Minimum Plan Dimension**. This is the shortest width/length of the soil area. Narrow, linear strips often fail stability tests even if they meet the total area volume.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div className="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-100 p-6 rounded-3xl flex gap-4">
